Madagascar Economy to Expand 2.8% in 2012, l’Express Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-10-13T08:04:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/madagascar-economy-to-expand-2-8-in-2012-l-express-says.html
Madagascar expects its economy to
expand 2.8 percent in 2012 and 0.8 percent this year, l’Express
de Madagascar said, citing Finance Minister Hery
Rajaonarimampianina.  Annual inflation is forecast to slow to 7.7 percent from
7.8 percent, the Antananarivo-based newspaper said on its
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
